verses.text:
This is a list of the cities and areas where the descendants of Ephraim lived:
\li1 Bethel and the nearby villages;
\li1 Naaran to the east;
\li1 Gezer to the west and the nearby villages; and
\li1 Shechem and the nearby villages. Those villages extended north as far as Ayyah and the nearby villages.
\li1

Ibneiah son of Jeroham;
\li1 Elah son of Uzzi; Uzzi son of Micri;
\li1 Meshullam son of Shephatiah; Shephatiah son of Reuel; Reuel son of Ibnijah.
\b
\li1

and Azariah son of Hilkiah.
\li2 Hilkiah son of Meshullam;
\li2 Meshullam son of Zadok,
\li2 Zadok son of Meraioth;
\li2 Meraioth son of Ahitub;
\li2 Ahitub, who was in charge of all the men who took care of the temple.
\li1

Adaiah son of Jeroham;
\li2 Jerohamson of Pashhur;
\li2 Pashhur son of Malchijah;
\li1 Maasai son of Adiel;
\li2 Adiel son of Jahzerah;
\li2 Jahzerah son of Meshullam;
\li2 Meshullam son of Meshillemith;
\li2 Meshillemith son of Immer.
\li1

From the descendants of Levi who returned to Judah there was: Shemaiah son of Hasshub;
\li2 Hasshub son of Azrikam;
\li2 Azrikam son of Hashabiah;
\li2 Hashabiah was a descendant of Levi's youngest son Merari.
\li1

Other descendants of Levi who returned to Judah were: Bakbakkar, Heresh, Galal, and Mattaniah son of Mica;
\li2 Mica son of Zicri;
\li2 Zicri son of Asaph;
\li1

There was also Obadiah son of Shemaiah;
\li2 Shemaiah son of Galal;
\li2 Galal son of Jeduthun;
\li1 There was also Berekiah son of Asa;
\li2 Asa son of Elkanah, who lived in one of the villages where the Netophath people lived.
\b
\li1

These are the names of the great warriors:
\li2 Asahel, younger brother of Joab;
\li2 Elhanan son of Dodo, from Bethlehem;
\li2

Shammah, from the Harod;
\li2 Helez, from the Pelon;
\li2

Ira son of Ikkesh, from Tekoa;
\li2 Abi Ezer, from Anathoth;
\li2

Sibbecai, from Hushah;
\li2 Ilai from Ahoh;
\li2

Maharai, from Netophah;
\li2 Heled, theson of Baanah, also from Netophah;
\li2

Ithai, son of Ribai, from Gibeah in the land that belonged to the tribe of Benjamin;
\li2 Benaiah, from Pirathon town;
\li2

Hurai, from the valleys near Mount Gaash;
\li2 Abiel from the clan of Arabah;
\li2

Azmaveth, from Baharum;
\li2 Eliahba, from Shaalbon;
\li2

The sons of Hashem from Gizon;
\li2 Jonathan son of Shagee from the Harar;
\li2

Ahiam son of Sharar from Harar;
\li2 Eliphal son of Ur;
\li2

Hepher from the Mekerath clan;
\li2 Ahijah from the Pelon;
\li2

Hezro from Carmel;
\li2 Naarai son of Ezbai;
\li2

Joel the younger brother of Nathan;
\li2 Mibhar son of Hagri;
\li2

Zelek from the Ammon people group;
\li2 Naharai, the man who carried Joab's weapons, from Beeroth;
\li2

Uriah, Bathsheba's husband, from the Heth people group;
\li2 Zabad son of Ahlai;
\li2

Hanan son of Maacah;
\li2 Joshaphat from Mithna;
\li2

Uzzia from Ashterath;
\li2 Shama and Jeiel, sons of Hotham, from Aroer.
\li2

Jediael son of Shimri
\li2 and his younger brother Joha, from Tiz town;
\li2

Eliel from Mahavah;
\li2 Jeribai and Joshaviah, sons of Elnaam;
\li2 Ithmah from the Moab;
\li2

Their leader was Ahiezer. Next in command was Joash. They were both sons of Shemaah from the city of Gibeah. These are the names of some of those warriors:
\li1 Jeziel and Pelet, sons of Azmaveth;
\li1 Beracah;
\li1 Jehu from the city of Anathoth;
\li1

Ishmaiah from the city of Gibeon, who was the leader of the thirty greatest warriors;
\li1 Jeremiah, Jahaziel, Johanan, and Jozabad from the city of Gederah;
\li1

Trust in Yahweh and in his power;
\q2 continually seek to get help from him.
\q1

He never forgets the covenants that he has made;
\q2 he made a promise that will last for a thousand generations.
\q1

He said that to them when there were only a few of them,
\q2 a tiny group of people who were living in that land like strangers;
\q1

Tell among the nations that he is great;
\q2 tell all the people groups the marvelous things that he has done.
\q1

The oceans and all the creatures that are in the oceans should shout;
\q2 the fields and everything that is in them should rejoice.
\q1

You alone are great and powerful;
\q2 only you are truly glorious and majestic and wonderful.
\q2 And that is true because everything in heaven and on the earth is yours.
\q1 You are the king of all the people in this world;
\q2 you are the ruler of everything.
\q1
